{
  "id": "019cf147-7430-7263-8c9f-52bd21e30a0d",
  "content": "## OpenVINO EP Root Cause: Missing ORT Provider Library (2026-03-15)\n\nThe `embedding_backend = \"openvino\"` config was accepted but ONNX Runtime silently fell back to CPU. Root cause: the `ort` crate's prebuilt ORT binary (from pyke.io, `cu12` feature set) does NOT include `libonnxruntime_providers_openvino.so`. The `openvino` Cargo feature only enables the Rust API types, not the actual EP provider.\n\n### Key Finding\n- `ort-sys` dist.txt has NO openvino variant — only cu12, wgpu, nvrtx, rocm, none\n- ORT core is statically linked, EP providers are dlopen'd at runtime\n- Binary has the error string: \"SessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_OpenVINO_V2: Failed to load shared library\"\n- iGPU frequency monitoring confirmed: 0-600 MHz (idle) during embedding load\n\n### Fix Deployed\n- Added `verify_ep_available()` to `embedding_service.rs` — calls `ort::ep::ExecutionProvider::is_available()`\n- `load_model()` detects missing EP and falls back to CPU with warning log\n- `model_manager.rs` queries actual backend after load — `corvia inference status` now shows truthful `cpu/cpu`\n- 3 new tests, all 42 tests pass\n\n### Blocking Item for iGPU Usage\nMust build ORT 1.23.2 from source with `-DUSE_OPENVINO=ON` to produce `libonnxruntime_providers_openvino.so`, then install alongside binary.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
